  "body": "### User Story\r\n\r\nAs a user, I want to see where a message is coming from when I receive a push notification.\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n*Type*: Bug\r\n\r\n*Summary*: Push notifications don't indicate where the message is coming from and the only way to know is by opening the app and searching for that message.\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\nShow origin of the message on a push notification.\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\nNothing indicates where the messages are coming from:\r\n\r\n<img width=\"353\" alt=\"captura de pantalla 2018-11-06 a la s 12 12 05 p m\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/37297779/48073394-6c7d0000-e1bd-11e8-8184-8e51f6ddc0b9.png\">\r\n\r\n<img width=\"354\" alt=\"captura de pantalla 2018-11-06 a la s 11 49 00 a m\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/37297779/48072721-f1671a00-e1bb-11e8-8eb4-c3250b28841a.png\">\r\n\r\n<img width=\"354\" alt=\"captura de pantalla 2018-11-06 a la s 12 02 28 p m\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/37297779/48072708-ed3afc80-e1bb-11e8-990a-c683631c0d11.png\">\r\n\r\n### Solution\r\nFor 1:1 chat, push notifications text should be:\r\n- Title: **{User-Name}**\r\n- Body: Message\r\n\r\n<img width=\"451\" alt=\"captura de pantalla 2018-11-06 a la s 12 09 08 p m\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/37297779/48073126-cdf09f00-e1bc-11e8-8ee3-69d852fd566a.png\">\r\n\r\nFor @mentions (feature TODO):\r\n- Title: \"**{User-Name} mentioned you**\"\r\n- Body: Mention message\r\n\r\n<img width=\"472\" alt=\"captura de pantalla 2018-11-06 a la s 12 10 51 p m\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/37297779/48073212-0f814a00-e1bd-11e8-9fb3-c189c3aa4ecf.png\">\r\n\r\nFor replies:\r\n- Title: \"**{User-Name} replied**\"\r\n- Body: Reply message\r\n\r\n<img width=\"468\" alt=\"captura de pantalla 2018-11-06 a la s 12 12 46 p m\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/37297779/48073351-540ce580-e1bd-11e8-9aab-68a285ffd6ec.png\">\r\n\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\nPlease note that we still don't have the mentions feature :) ",
